	   <tr><td colspan=2>So let's get this straight... I'm in the middle of combat and it's starting to hit the fan.&nbsp;&nbsp;Running is not an option so I whip out my OT hammer, start swinging, and hope that it procs and transports me to the relative safety of the OT outpost?  I just got mine the other night and haven't played with it yet, but if it is a proc and not a right-clickable effect, then I'm starting to think the value of this item isn't what I thought it was.  I was hoping that I could just carry this around and right click it at whim for a fool-proof x-loc.  Any insight on this subject, maybe a suggestion of more efficient utilization would be much appreciated.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
